div.head:
166. Minutes of Washington Special Actions Group MeetingSource: National Archives, Nixon Presidential Materials, NSC Files, NSC Institutional Files (H-Files), Box H–116, WSAG Minutes, Originals, 1972. Top Secret;
                            Sensitive. The meeting was held in the White House Situation
                            Room.

div.p:
—We want to be sure that we make available whatever is needed to defend Laos;
                        if that means a request for a ceiling increase later, we will have to
                        consider it.

b) Use up resources which we could otherwise use to improve the chances for a
                        peaceful social evolution in the Philippines and diminish the danger of
                        chaos and explosive revolution—objectives 3, 4 and 5;

A. Peking view of Japan (we said Peking very worried about revival of
                        militarism, though in fact internal restraints in Japan against militarism
                        remain very strong);

B. Whether China still thinks in terms of encirclement (yes, but Soviets have
                        replaced U.S. as number one threat and China may begin to perceive
                        advantages in our overall posture of involvement);
